lair /lɛə/

1. N-COUNT A lair is a place where a wild animal lives, usually a place which is underground or well-hidden. 兽穴; 兽窝 [usu with poss] 

例： ...a fox's lair. ...一个狐狸窝。 

2. N-COUNT Someone's lair is the particular room or hiding place that they go to, especially when they want to get away from other people. 藏匿之所; 隐避之处 [非正式] [usu with poss] 

例： The village was once a pirates' lair. 这个村子曾一度是海盗藏匿之处。

